Ladies Riding Chaps & Chain Shirt/Leather & Metal Bottom
Ladies Riding Chaps & Chain Shirt/Leather Bottom

The club is a very basic weapon, usually consisting of nothing more than a tapered length of hardwood.

This particular club is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

This OOC item represents the ownership of a ridable horse.  You may bring it with you in party, ride it, or tie it up in place.  It cannot be "de-spawned" unless you log out.   The item must be equipped to be used.   The major use of the item is to dismount a horse, though it may also be used to reclaim the horse when close to it, if the horse will not respond to conversation attempts.

Most horse options are handled via a private conversation with the horse.

-Mount the horse
Once mounted, the reigns are equipped into your off-hand, and the horse provides a movement speed increase. If combat is entered while mounted, ride skill checks (DC 20) will be necessary to stay on the back of a horse which was not trained for war. Should the reigns be unequipped in combat, riding skill checks are necessary to be able to control the mount with your knees (DC 5).

-Tie the horse up
This will leave the horse in a specific location. It will re-spawn in this location next time you enter the server.

-Untie the horse
This will bring the horse with you.

-Name the horse
Allows you to give the horse a custom name, that will persist across ownership transfers.

Trade or sale of the horse can be accomplished by trade or sale of this item. 

ALFA Rules on horse use:
-Same policy against OOC running as applies to unmounted PCs.  You may gallop on the horse for short distances, but walking/canter is the usual case.

-Horses may not be brought into caves, dungeons, etc.

-Horses are not intended as combat tools/meat shields.  Any suspicious use of warhorses in combat will lead to suspension of horse use rights.

Should the reigns be unequipped in combat, riding skill checks are necessary to be able to control the mount with your knees (DC 5).

-Tie the horse up
This will leave the horse in a specific location. It will re-spawn in this location next time you enter the server.

-Untie the horse
This will bring the horse with you.

-Name the horse
Allows you to give the horse a custom name, that will persist across ownership transfers.

Trade or sale of the horse can be accomplished by trade or sale of this item. 

ALFA Rules on horse use:
-Same policy against OOC running as applies to unmounted PCs.  You may gallop on the horse for short distances, but walking/canter is the usual case.

-Horses may not be brought into caves, dungeons, etc.

-Horses are not intended as combat tools/meat shields.  Any suspicious use of warhorses in combat will lead to suspension of horse use rights.
